This paper focuses on using social network data to predict social status, which falls under the categories of social networks and computational social science. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) are the most likely categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges and limitations of this approach, which could fall under the categories of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER), information retrieval (cs.IR), and natural language processing (cs.CL).
